<br>
Apples oranges.<br>
<br>
But to the meat of the article. I am biased being a 65 paladin. I agree with many said things. I beleive that changing the taunt to some degree will not appease those who wish things go back to the old days when no one wanted a paladin or sk and only by shear detmination did one prove worthy and be asked again to groups.<br>
<br>
But lets play along for a minute. If warriors were to be given a &quot;Better&quot; taunt. How much would be better? 5%, 10% 30% ? I meran you cant have a warrior who has 100% taunt.. it would trivilize the content! So what number works?<br>
<br>
Bu then the people want to say &quot;Hey knights have almost 100% aggro! we want it too!&quot; I see that you may think its 100% but its not. But lets say for the sake of argument that casting a 3 second (Plus or minus a swcond or 2 depending on which stun or other type spell you are casting) is instant 100% aggro. The knight must and does pay a penalty! That penalty for that ability is... well look above! So what may make us desirable (and I have always felt to LAZY exp groups) to exp groups makes us a drawback to higher end content. <br>
<br>
You can not trivilize that! So if you get 100% aggro are you willing to give up the other things you get? Well then your a knight. And knights if you get the items that Warriors have are you willing to give up your abilities?<br>
<br>
The main problem is (Please let me interject and say that a small upping of taunt is totally agreeable to me and most levelheaded knights) as I see it is Groups are lazy!!!<br>
<br>
1. Knight group.... Knight pulls .. gets aggro all nuke  cleric has to heal quicker. Group has to kill quicker! Why? well the knight does not have the ability at ANY time to mitigate the damage or absorb the damage to equally equipped warrior.<br>
<br>
2. Warrior group.... War pulls ... war works on aggr... then slowly the group slows and nukes. Mob dies a fraction later thaqn knight group but... Group has more mana.. (Less heals and less nukes).<br>
<br>
What I see is groups that have a warrior as main tank and NOT THE WARRIOR are the messed up ones. The shammy/chanter have to relearn like we all did in the past that you dont nuke or slow till approx 90 or 95%.... You dont chain nuke... you dont sit after a large dot or nuke. But they blame the warrior for not having 100% aggr?<br>
<br>
So in summary I agree that warriors need an inate 5 or 10% higher aggro success rate maybe I can be convinced to maybeeven 65% success rate.<br>
<br>
Or add in a hate modifier for each taunt of like 100 even if fail. That may cause more button mashers than before but at least they would get a payout <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Till then Groups need to stop putting the blame on warriors and look at thier tactics!!!!!!!!!!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doene80>doene80</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/25/03 4:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2113.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dark Truths in Class Balance</span><hr size=1> I just figured I'd clear up a point or two. I am not mad at the way warriors are acting because with how things are at this point, the class is broken, unwanted and unused. what I disagree with is how some (but not all) warriors think the only way to balance the game again is to make knights how they were in kunark ages. I dont agree with nerfing any class. What I do want is to see warriors more desirable again, but not so far as to make knights unwanted again, and I know it will take some time before warriors are getting called to groups again. because alot of people arent gonna see this new melee system right away. All I want is some sort of balance brought to the table but not by making Knights undesirable to the point it was back in the day. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Doene Laforge</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
